Từ điển Đồng nghĩa
belonging
▸ noun AFFILIATION, acceptance, association, attachment, integration, closeness; rapport, fellow feeling, fellowship.
Opposites
alienation.

sentences.en: In certain working situations, belonging to the upper crust can create more problems than belonging to the underprivileged classes.

sentences.en: Firms belonging to Southern-born managers were easily the most successful, while firms belonging to northern-born managers operating in the south clearly were the least successful.

sentences.en: After many years here, I feel a strong sense of belonging.

sentences.en: Church is used only before noun to mean something belonging to or connected with a church.

sentences.en: The Betel is the leaf of a vine belonging to the Piperaceae family.

sentences.en: Values make military members feel good about belonging to the unit.
